// TEST: stdlib_error_output_smoke
// EXPECT: output "boom"
//
// A `main` that constructs an error via `core.error.error(...)` and prints its
// message. The conformance execution lane (#372) walks the whole tree and runs
// every `// EXPECT: output` fixture, so this is compiled and executed on each
// present target, stdout-diffed against the directive above. The richer
// field/method-name collision lock for `core.error` (`.message()` method vs the
// `message` field) lives in `conformance/exec/exec_core_error.bock`, which reads
// both members on all five targets (the Q-go-error-message fix is locked there).
// This fixture is also validated by the CLI-level `bock run` smoke test in
// bock-cli's `stdlib_error` integration suite against the interpreter.
module main

use core.error.{error}

public fn main() {
  println(error("boom").message())
}
